# Hermes Mobile verification

When editing anything under `hermes-mobile/`:

1. Run unit tests in the same turn: `cd hermes-mobile && npm test -- --no-coverage --watchman=false`
2. Trigger autonomous E2E (do not tell the user to run Maestro):
   ```bash
   launchctl kickstart -k "gui/$(id -u)/com.igor.hermes-mobile-continuous-e2e" 2>/dev/null \
     || (cd hermes-mobile && npm run e2e:continuous:once)
   ```
3. Read `hermes-mobile/docs/proofs/continuous/latest.json` before claiming chat/UI is fixed.
4. Phone setup: `node tools/hermes-mobile-pair.js` when `adb devices` shows a device — never manual Settings steps.
5. **Brand-new user mindset** — every test assumes a stranger: no adb, no dev backdoor, release build, realistic network. See [hermes-mobile-real-users.mdc](./hermes-mobile-real-users.mdc).

Full contract: [hermes-mobile/AGENTS.md](../../hermes-mobile/AGENTS.md).
